name: George Restaurant & Bar

reviews.review_text: George Restaurant and Bar in Goa is a true gem! Established in 1956, it offers a fantastic blend of history and delicious food. I tried the beef, crab, chicken, and bun, and everything was exceptionally tasty. The flavors are authentic, and the service is warm. A must-visit for food lovers!

Went for an early dinner, on a weekday.
This restaurant is recommended for Goan cuisine.
We go there mainly for their meat preparations.
Starters:
Beef salted tongue, Pork cream chop, sausage pao (bread) - all good, & Bombay duck rava fried (v. mediocre).
Mains: Beef pulav (super, sharing portion).
Dessert: Caramel pudding. (no other Dessert on the menu!)
Except for the fish (Bombil),  the food was enjoyable.
Service good.
Ambiance somewhat noisy, as faces the busy road traffic.
They serve alcohol - no alcohol menu though,  for reasons best known to them.
Would recommend this place for a decent Goan meal, mainly for the meats.

I recently visited George restaurant and bar and I was utterly appalled by the experience. After a forgettable meal, nature called, and I politely asked to use the restroom. To my shock and disbelief, the staff refused. Yes, you read that correctly—denied access to a basic facility that any paying customer should be entitled to.

The excuse? “Only paying customers can use the restroom.” I had already ordered food and drinks, mind you, and was in the middle of eating. Not only was this policy incredibly bizarre, but it also felt downright disrespectful. There is absolutely no reason a customer should be treated like this, and it’s completely against the spirit of hospitality.

The staff was unhelpful and cold when I asked for clarification, and it left a really bad taste in my mouth—literally and figuratively. I will NEVER return to a place that doesn’t have the decency to provide basic customer service or common human decency. If you’re looking for a place that values basic courtesy and respect, look elsewhere.

description:
**Dining at George Restaurant & Bar: A Culinary Journey in Goa**

Nestled in the lively Corlim Industrial Estate, George Restaurant & Bar is a longstanding culinary fixture that has earned a commendable rating of 4.1 from nearly 1,100 enthusiastic patrons. Renowned for its Goan cuisine, the restaurant frequently garners specific acclaim for its **exquisite pork dishes** (41 mentions) and a variety of **prawn preparations** (19 mentions), making it a delightful choice for meat lovers. While **alcohol** (8 mentions) is available to complement meals, the establishment has received mixed feedback regarding its beverage offerings.

**Ambiance & Design**

Stepping into George Restaurant & Bar, guests are welcomed by an ambiance that strikes a balance between nostalgia and understated charm. Established back in 1956, the interiors reflect the restaurant’s rich history with warm lighting that invites comfort. According to customer feedback and visual impressions from shared photos, the décor includes rustic wooden accents and tasteful arrangements that hint at classic Goan traditions, although some reviews noted that the noise from the nearby road could detract from a more tranquil dining experience. The images convey a bustling yet inviting atmosphere, perfect for casual gatherings but perhaps not for intimate dinners.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at George is a homage to traditional Goan flavors, with a special emphasis on meat dishes. Signature items such as **beef salted tongue**, **pork cream chop**, and **sausage pao** stand out as fan favorites among guests, praised for their authenticity and rich taste. One customer highlights the **beef pulav** as a must-try for sharing, representing the kind of hearty meal patrons can relish together. Desserts are somewhat limited, with **caramel pudding** being the sole option offered, leaving room for future menu exploration. The presentation of food, documented through vibrant customer photos, showcases a careful attention to detail—a visual feast that tempts the taste buds.

For those with dietary restrictions, George Restaurant & Bar may need to provide clearer indications on vegetarian alternatives, as feedback seemed to favor meat-centric offerings.

**Customer Experience & Service**

The experience at George, however, hasn’t been uniformly positive. While many reviews commend the warmth of the staff and the generally efficient service, there are exceptions. A particularly disheartening experience was recounted by a dissatisfied customer who faced a refusal to use restroom facilities, even after having placed an order. This incident raised significant eyebrows, painting a picture of inconsistency in service culture that contradicts the restaurant's hospitality spirit. Nonetheless, many customers encourage others to visit, noting that the food alone is worth the experience.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Online buzz surrounding George Restaurant & Bar has been predominantly positive, with posts celebrating its vibrant dishes and lively setting widely shared. However, the contrasting service experiences suggest there’s room for improvement in customer relations. Despite the mixed reviews, the establishment remains a local favorite—especially among those eager to dive into the depths of Goan cuisine.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

Supporting these narratives are various customer photos that showcase not only the tempting dishes but also the restaurant's welcoming interiors. Visual highlights include shots of well-presented meals that are sure to entice anyone scrolling through social platforms. These images effectively communicate the restaurant’s commitment to its culinary roots, evoking a sense of nostalgia and pride in its long-standing heritage.

In conclusion, George Restaurant & Bar stands as a noteworthy establishment within Goa’s dining landscape, offering an array of hearty dishes that reflect the rich culinary culture of the region. While some aspects of the service may warrant consideration, the flavorful experience and historic charm of the restaurant remain strong draws for both locals and tourists alike.
